# Google API for Gmail
# IMPORTANT: To use Gmail integration, you need to:
# 1. Create a Google Cloud Project at https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Enable the Gmail API in APIs & Services > Library
# 3. Create credentials (API Key and OAuth 2.0 Client ID)
# 4. Add your domain/localhost to authorized origins
VITE_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
VITE_GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/auth/google/callback

# Gmail Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Go to "APIs & Services" > "Library"
# 4. Search for "Gmail API" and click "Enable"
# 5. Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials"
# 6. Create API Key and OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# 7. For OAuth Client ID, add these authorized origins:
#    - http://localhost:5173
#    - https://your-domain.com (for production)
# 8. Copy the API Key to VITE_GOOGLE_API_KEY
# 9. Copy the Client ID to VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID